Hello,

I am a beginner trying to figure out the temperature limitations on
Canteras chemical equilibrium calculations. From what I understand
Cantera uses the same data as GRI-Mech 3.0 for these calculations,
correct? If so it uses a seven digit polynomial fit of molar heat
capacity, entropy and standard enthalpy of formation values and it
uses this fit to find values in the temperature range 200K-3000K, correct?
 
My problem is that I need a code that can calculate (in the cases
where data exists) up to 20000K, or even higher if possible. I know
that this is possible to do with CEA but it would save me a lot of
work if I could do it with a program that is Matlab compatible (such
as Cantera). Is it at all possible?

Thanks,
           Tomas
